content:
It sounds like that backpacking trip had a profound impact on you! Being in nature, surrounded by the beauty and majesty of the Rocky Mountains, can be a powerful catalyst for reflection and self-discovery.

There's something about immersing yourself in the natural world, disconnecting from the hustle and bustle of daily life, and challenging yourself physically and mentally that can help clarify your priorities and values.

What did you learn about yourself and your priorities during that trip? Was there a particular moment or experience that stood out to you?
